{"title_page": "Central Bank of Costa Rica", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{more footnotes|date=April 2015}}\n{{more citations needed|date=April 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox Central bank\n|image_1= Banco Central de Costa Rica.jpg\n|image_title_1 = Central Bank of Costa Rica building in [[San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica|San Jos\u00e9]]\n|image_width_1 = 150px\n|bank_name_in_local =Banco Central de Costa Rica\n|headquarters = \n|established = January 1950\n|president = Rodrigo Cubero Brealey\n|leader_title = Governor\n|bank_of = [[Costa Rica]]\n|currency = [[Costa Rican col\u00f3n]]\n|currency_iso = \n|reserves =\n|website = {{URL|www.bccr.fi.cr/}}\n|preceded = \n|succeeded =\n|footnotes =\n}}\nThe '''Central Bank of Costa Rica''' ({{lang-es|Banco Central de Costa Rica}}) is the [[central bank]] of [[Costa Rica]]. It is recognized by the Costa Rican society and the international community for its efficiency, transparency and credibility in keeping inflation low and stable.\n\n==Scope==\nIn pursuit of its mission, and to maintain the economy\u2019s internal and external balance, the goals and operating objectives of the Central Bank of Costa Rica are as follows:\n\n* Maintain internal stability of the national currency, seeking to turn the full employment of productive resources. \n* Maintain external stability of the national currency and ensure their free conversion to other currencies. \n* Promote a stable system of financial intermediation, efficient and competitive.\n\nSimilar to other Central Banks in the world, the functions of Central Bank of Costa Rica include providing banking services to the Government of Costa Rica and financial institutions, issuing the domestic currency, regulating commercial banks and other financial institutions, providing economic advice to the Government, conducting research and publishing information on monetary and other economic developments. Only notes and coins issued by the Central Bank shall be legal tender in [[Costa Rica]].\n\n==Presidents==\n*[[Juan Dent Alvarado]]\n*[[Jaime Solera Bennett]]\n*[[Rodrigo Facio Brenes]]\n*[[Carlos Manuel Escalante Duran]], 1962-?\n*[[Rodolfo Lara Iraeta]] ? -1965-1967-?\n*[[Juan Rafael Arias]], ?-1970-?\n*[[Bernal Jim\u00e9nez Monge]], 1973-1974\n*[[Juan Jos\u00e9 Arrea Escalante]], ?-1978\n*[[Guillermo Gonz\u00e1lez Truque]], 1978-1980\n*[[Manuel Naranjo Coto]], 1980-1981-?\n*[[Carlos Manuel Castillo Morales]], 1982-1984\n*[[Eduardo Lizano]], 1984-1990\n*[[Jorge Guardia Quir\u00f3s]], 1990-1993\n*[[Carlos Manuel Castillo Morales]], 1994-1995\n*[[Rodrigo Bola\u00f1os]], 1995-1998\n*[[Eduardo Lizano Fait]], 1998-2002\n*[[Francisco de Paula Guti\u00e9rrez]], 2002-2010\n*[[Rodrigo Bola\u00f1os]], 2010-2014\n*[[Olivier Castro P\u00e9rez]], 2014-2018\n*[[Rodrigo Cubero Brealey]], 2018-\n<ref>https://www.academiaca.or.cr/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Volatilidad_y_Vulnerabilidad.pdf</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Banco Nacional de Costa Rica|BICSA]]\n* [[Costa Rican col\u00f3n]]\n* [[Pre-Columbian Gold Museum]]\n* [[Economy of Costa Rica]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|es}} [http://www.bccr.fi.cr/ Official site of Banco Central de Costa Rica]\n{{Central Bank by country}}\n{{Central banks}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Central banks|Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Banks of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:1950 establishments in Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 1950]]\n\n\n{{bank-stub}}\n{{CostaRica-gov-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{no footnotes|date=April 2015}}\n{{refimprove|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox Central bank\n|image_1= Banco Central de Costa Rica.jpg\n|image_title_1 = Central Bank of Costa Rica building in [[San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica|San Jos\u00e9]]\n|image_width_1 = 150px\n|bank_name_in_local =Banco Central de Costa Rica\n|headquarters = \n|established = January 1950\n|president = Rodrigo Cubero Brealey\n|leader_title = Governor\n|bank_of = [[Costa Rica]]\n|currency = [[Costa Rican col\u00f3n]]\n|currency_iso = \n|reserves =\n|website = {{URL|www.bccr.fi.cr/}}\n|preceded = \n|succeeded =\n|footnotes =\n}}\nThe '''Central Bank of Costa Rica''' ({{lang-es|Banco Central de Costa Rica}}) is the [[central bank]] of [[Costa Rica]]. It is recognized by the Costa Rican society and the international community for its efficiency, transparency and credibility in keeping inflation low and stable.\n\n==Scope==\nIn pursuit of its mission, and to maintain the economy\u2019s internal and external balance, the goals and operating objectives of the Central Bank of Costa Rica are as follows:\n\n* Maintain internal stability of the national currency, seeking to turn the full employment of productive resources. \n* Maintain external stability of the national currency and ensure their free conversion to other currencies. \n* Promote a stable system of financial intermediation, efficient and competitive. \n\nSimilar to other Central Banks in the world, the functions of Central Bank of Costa Rica include providing banking services to the Government of Costa Rica and financial institutions, issuing the domestic currency, regulating commercial banks and other financial institutions, providing economic advice to the Government, conducting research and publishing information on monetary and other economic developments. Only notes and coins issued by the Central Bank shall be legal tender in [[Costa Rica]].\n\n==Presidents==\n*[[Juan Dent Alvarado]]\n*[[Jaime Solera Bennett]]\n*[[Rodrigo Facio Brenes]]\n*[[Carlos Manuel Escalante Duran]], 1962-?\n*[[Rodolfo Lara Iraeta]] ? -1965-1967-?\n*[[Juan Rafael Arias]], ?-1970-?\n*[[Bernal Jim\u00e9nez Monge]], 1973-1974\n*[[Juan Jos\u00e9 Arrea Escalante]], ?-1978\n*[[Guillermo Gonz\u00e1lez Truque]], 1978-1980\n*[[Manuel Naranjo Coto]], 1980-1981-?\n*[[Carlos Manuel Castillo Morales]], 1982-1984\n*[[Eduardo Lizano]], 1984-1990\n*[[Jorge Guardia Quir\u00f3s]], 1990-1993\n*[[Carlos Manuel Castillo Morales]], 1994-1995\n*[[Rodrigo Bola\u00f1os]], 1995-1998\n*[[Eduardo Lizano Fait]], 1998-2002\n*[[Francisco de Paula Guti\u00e9rrez]], 2002-2010\n*[[Rodrigo Bola\u00f1os]], 2010-2014\n*[[Olivier Castro P\u00e9rez]], 2014-2018\n*[[Rodrigo Cubero Brealey]], 2018-\n<ref>https://www.academiaca.or.cr/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Volatilidad_y_Vulnerabilidad.pdf</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Banco Nacional de Costa Rica|BICSA]]\n* [[Costa Rican col\u00f3n]]\n* [[Pre-Columbian Gold Museum]]\n* [[Economy of Costa Rica]]\n<!-- ==References==\n<references /> -->\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|es}} [http://www.bccr.fi.cr/ Official site of Banco Central de Costa Rica]\n{{Central Bank by country}}\n{{Central banks}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Central banks|Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Banks of Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:1950 establishments in Costa Rica]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 1950]]\n\n{{bank-stub}}\n{{CostaRica-gov-stub}}\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reflist", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_Bank_of_Costa_Rica"}
