ation_demonym      =\n| population_note         =\n| timezone1               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset1             = +01\n| timezone1_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset1_DST         = +02\n| postal_code_type        =\n| postal_code             =\n| area_code_type          =\n| area_code               =\n| iso_code                =\n| website                 = <!-- [http://www.example.com example.com] -->\n| footnotes               =\n}}\nThe '''Municipality of Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih Goricah''' ({{IPA-sl|\u02c8s\u028be\u02d0ti \u02c8ju\u02d0\u027eii\u032f \u028d sl\u0254\u02c8\u028be\u02d0nski\u0263 \u0261\u0254\u02c8\u027ei\u02d0tsax|pron}}; {{lang-sl|Ob\u010dina Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih goricah}}) is a [[municipality]] in northeastern [[Slovenia]]. It was created in 2006 when it separated from the [[Municipality of Lenart]]. It lies at the western end of the [[Slovenske Gorice|Slovene Hills]] ({{lang-sl|Slovenske gorice}}). Its administrative centre is in [[Jurovski Dol]]. The area was part of the traditional region of [[Lower Styria|Styria]]. It is now included in the [[Drava Statistical Region]].<ref>[http://www.obcinajurij.si Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih Goricah municipal site]</ref>\n\nThe municipality gets its name from the local [[parish church]] in Jurovski Dol, dedicated to [[Saint George]] ({{lang-sl|sveti Jurij}}).<ref>[http://rkd.situla.org/ Slovenian Ministry of Culture register of national heritage] reference number e\u0161d 3050</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{commonscat-inline|Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih goricah municipality|Municipality of Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih Goricah}}\n*[http://www.obcinajurij.si Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih Goricah municipal site]\n*[http://www.geopedia.si/Geopedia_en.html?params=L408_F210_T973_vF_b4_x561218.656_y163539.465_s13 Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih Goricah on Geopedia]\n\n{{Sveti Jurij v Slovenskih Goricah}}\n{{Municipalities of Slovenia}}\n[[Cate